{
  "name": "Run FSM Approval Regression Tests",
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "description": "Complete approval regression testing workflow: Parse TES-070, Create test instructions, Execute tests via subagent",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "UNIVERSAL FSM APPROVAL REGRESSION TESTING WORKFLOW\n\nThis hook orchestrates the complete approval testing workflow and delegates execution to specialized subagents.\n\nPHASE 1: GATHER INFORMATION\n1. List clients in Projects/ - user selects\n2. List TES-070 documents in Projects/{ClientName}/TES-070/Approval_TES070s_For_Regression_Testing/ - user selects\n3. Prompt for FSM credentials (URL, username, password, environment)\n4. Save credentials to Projects/{ClientName}/Credentials/ (.env.fsm and .env.passwords)\n\nPHASE 2: PARSE TES-070 AND DETECT TRANSACTION TYPE\n5. Run: python ReusableTools/tes070_analyzer.py \"<tes070_path>\"\n6. Read the generated _analysis.json file\n7. Extract transaction type from document (ExpenseInvoice, ManualJournal, CashLedgerTransaction)\n   - Look for keywords in title/description: \"Expense Invoice\", \"Manual Journal\", \"Cash Ledger\"\n   - Default to ExpenseInvoice if unclear\n8. Map transaction type to specialized subagent:\n   - ExpenseInvoice -> invoice-approval-test-agent\n   - ManualJournal -> journal-approval-test-agent (NOT YET CREATED)\n   - CashLedgerTransaction -> cash-approval-test-agent (NOT YET CREATED)\n\nPHASE 3: VALIDATE SUBAGENT EXISTS\n9. Check if required subagent exists in .kiro/agents/\n10. If subagent does NOT exist:\n    - Display error: \"Transaction type {type} requires {agent-name} which is not yet created\"\n    - List available agents in .kiro/agents/\n    - Stop execution\n    - Suggest: Create the required subagent or use a different TES-070 document\n11. If subagent exists: Continue to Phase 4\n\nPHASE 4: CREATE TEST INSTRUCTIONS JSON\n12. Run: python ReusableTools/create_test_instructions.py \"<analysis_json_path>\" \"Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/approval/{extension_id}_test_instructions.json\"\n13. This script:\n    - Reads TES-070 analysis JSON\n    - Extracts scenarios with test_steps (skips TOC entries)\n    - Creates simplified test instructions JSON\n    - Includes scenario title, description, test_steps, expected_results\n14. Validate JSON: python ReusableTools/validate_json.py \"<test_instructions_json_path>\"\n15. If validation fails: Display error and stop\n\nPHASE 5: INVOKE SPECIALIZED TESTING SUBAGENT\n16. Invoke subagent with prompt:\n    \"Execute approval tests for {ClientName}.\n    \n    Test Instructions JSON: {test_instructions_json_path}\n    FSM URL: {url}\n    Username: {username}\n    Password: {password}\n    Environment: {environment}\n    \n    Read the test instructions JSON file.\n    For each scenario, execute the test_steps using MCP Playwright tools.\n    Interpret each step description and execute the appropriate browser actions.\n    Take snapshots before every action to find element refs.\n    Capture screenshots after each critical step.\n    Save screenshots to: Projects/{ClientName}/Temp/evidence/\n    Document pass/fail results for each scenario.\"\n\n17. Subagent executes tests autonomously using MCP Playwright\n18. Subagent reports results\n\nPHASE 6: DISPLAY SUMMARY\n19. Show final summary with pass/fail counts, screenshot locations\n\nCURRENTLY AVAILABLE AGENTS:\n- invoice-approval-test-agent: Handles ExpenseInvoice approval workflows (Payables module)\n\nFUTURE AGENTS (Not yet created):\n- journal-approval-test-agent: Will handle ManualJournal approval workflows (GL module)\n- cash-approval-test-agent: Will handle CashLedgerTransaction approval workflows (Cash module)\n\nCRITICAL NOTES:\n- The create_test_instructions.py script extracts test scenarios from TES-070 analysis\n- The subagent reads test_steps and interprets them into MCP Playwright actions\n- The subagent MUST use MCP Playwright tools directly (mcp_playwright_browser_*)\n- The subagent takes snapshots before every action to find element refs\n- The subagent is autonomous and makes decisions based on what it sees\n\nYOU ARE THE AGENT EXECUTING THIS WORKFLOW. Begin with Phase 1 immediately."
  },
  "enabled": true
}